A total of four major questions have been selected by the Esa, on which the missions of the 2007 programme "Cosmic Vision" are to find answers.
What are the conditions for the creation of planets and lives?
The exact processes of the emergence of stars from large gas clouds - and thus also the formation of planets surrounding these stars - are still in the dictionary darkness.
A large infrared telescope in space could penetrate this darkness.
And if a star has planets, under what circumstances can life arise there?
To look into this issue, the space telescope "Cheops" will be launched in 2017, with which 500 already known planetary systems in our closest surroundings will be examined more closely.
