Douglas Kidd of the Passenger Association National Association of Airline Passengers said that he considered the disturbance of the equipment to be real, even if the risk was minimal.
Other committee members said that there were only isolated reports from pilots who spoke for a disturbance of aircraft systems through the equipment, and most of them were very old.
However, the Committee recommended that the FAA allow pilots to order the switching off of the equipment by passengers in the event of instrumental landing under poor conditions.
